YOU ARE BULLIES, NOT AGGRESSIVELY PROTECTING YOUR BRAND.

So, Adidas is a pretty big deal, isn't it? They make clothes, shoes, and all sorts of sports gear. And let's be honest, we've all owned a pair of those classic three-stripe track pants at some point in our lives.

But have you noticed how every time a new Adidas shoe drops, people go absolutely crazy for it? Like, standing-in-line-for-hours-crazy? It's like they're giving away free money or something.

And don't even get me started on the collaborations Adidas does with celebrities. I mean, Kanye West has his own shoe line with them. Kanye! The same guy who tweets about being in debt and yet somehow has millions of fans willing to shell out hundreds of dollars for his sneakers.

But you know what really surprises me? How everyone pronounces "Adidas" differently. Some people say "a-DEED-as," some say "ad-EYE-das," and some people just give up and call it "that fancy brand with the stripes."

Personally, I'm not a sneakerhead or a fashion guru, so I just stick to my old, beaten-up pair of Adidas running shoes. They might not be the latest and greatest, but they get the job done. And hey, at least I don't have to wait in line for hours or pronounce the name wrong.

El 16/05/23 compre dos pares de zapatillas en la tienda Adidas de Gran Vía, Madrid, España; las Solar Glide 6 y las Boston 11. Las Solar las he usado en varias oportunidades para entrenar, no he tenido problema alguno, pero las Boston 11 me han causado daño en cada oportunidad que la he usado, las use un par de martes, en entrenamiento de series y una carrera. Me causaron abrasión en la parte posterior del Tobillo, en cada ocasión, una herida desagradable en cada pie que me impedía seguir entrenando.

El 18 de Julio de 2023 me acerque a la tienda Adidas Gran Vía con el propósito, tras plantear la situación, de cambiar las zapatillas, no tuve suerte, de manera amable me invitaron a seguir usando las zapatillas que me causan heridas.

Este asunto me genera un poco de malestar, luego de tanto años de usar adidas, primera vez que me hace daño una zapatilla, esperaba otro tipo de atención, un poco de compresión de parte de Adidas.

Escribo con la intención de solicitar ayuda al respecto.

Quedo atento a sus comentarios.
